snippet.textDisplay:
Seeing the comment section and this video is like reliving the memories back in February in China.
Everything shuts down and government urges everyone to stay home. Factories, business asks employees to WFH and school postpone opening from CNY holiday.
Those were times with fear and anxiousness, people staying on social media tracking numbers , which is like skyrocketing everyday.
There were negativity, as we saw in the beginning people were divided, xenophobic, sometimes even calling out those who came down with the virus and those in deep hot water in Wuhan.
There were also tears when we heard another front-line nurses and doctors hit with the virus and passed.
Luckily, there were also warmth, reason and compassion. Social media were flushed with donation posts. I saw people retweeting tips of sanitizing, coordinating resources for hospitals in severe shortage. I saw new businesses programming infographics that updates and analyses numbers everyday. I saw self-media channel clarifying on rumors and misinformation. I saw people, city cleaners, delivery men, drivers, community workers keeps working to keep cities from malfunctioning and people’s life from disruptions.
There were jokes and self entertainment, like come on guys, this will be the only time in your life you could stay at home, doing nothing, still getting paid from your boss and contributing to the whole society 😂.
Looking back, that time was tough, a lot times messy, but everyone were less divided and anxious but more informed and on the same page as the virus progressed: let’s do everything right to get this ended.
Well China are still hanging in there fighting the last bit of those in Wuhan. But if we could come through all this, the US will too.
Stay strong 💪
Oh, forgot to say that China and the US are so different in ideology and often times don’t see eye to eye.
But when it came to needs and emotions, we are all human and we are more similar than we are different.
So a tip to stay emotionally strong individually in this special time, just ignore the hatred, foolishness or negativity that appeared on social media, be positive, give sympathy and find the right, objective information sources.
And forgive yourself if you are panicking or feeling down or afraid , we are just human but try to overcome with good senses and reason.

snippet.textDisplay:
Don't forget that even if you are healthy and not at risk, you CAN carry the virus and infect other people. COVID 19 often does not have severe effects on healthy people, but, nevertheless, limit your contacts with others for those two weeks. Yes, we here in Italy find ways to cheer us up, but we still have 32000 infected and almost 2000 cases in ICU (on a total number of 5000 ICU). Social distancing is not meant to avoid you from getting infected, as much as it might sound strange; it is meant to avoid the healthcare system to collapse. The US have less than 100k ICUs and a population of over 300 million... do the maths.

Stay safe and stay at home. It all will pass, if we work together as one
